Information über die Indikation, Behandlungskonzepte, Wirkung und eventuell unerwünschte Begleitreaktionen übersichtlich aufzeigt. Es ist somit ein praxisorientiertes Nachschlagewerk im klinischen Alltag am Patienten.  aRadiosurgery has been established for over 30 years for treating diseases in the brain. CyberKnife surgery has made it possible to kill malignant tumors throughout the body by means of concentrated radiation, thereby avoiding an operation or chemotherapy. This practical work describes methodology, clinical indications, treatment approaches, efficacy, and potential adverse effects.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Apr 2022) 0aBrainxSurgery. 0aRobotics in medicine. 0aSurgical robots. 7aMEDICAL / Clinical Medicine.2bisacsh1 aBecker, Gerd, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBecker, Gerd, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aBleif, Martin, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBleif, Martin, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aCelik, Eren, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDettinger, Boris, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFürweger, Christoph, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGrün, Arne, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHaidenberger, Alfred, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKocher, Martin, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKocher, Martin, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aKufeld, Markus, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMarnitz-Schulze, Simone, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMuacevic, Alexander, 